oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Receipt from the office of the Adjutant General, Department of Tennessee and Georgia, G.A.R.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This Grand Army of the Republic receipt was received from "James George, Comd'r Post No. 32, Quartermaster's Reports" for 3rd Quarter, 1886 in the amount of $3.30. James George served as a sergeant in Co. B (later Co. A), 1st Tenn. Inf. Regt., USA.
